    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; all achieved levels fall below required levels for MRL 5. Six factors were flagged as not-assessed epistemic gaps. The primary hemolysis index comparison (ValidationResult morrison-cou2-primary-hemolysis-index) demonstrates NIH agreement within 18% across five operating points with Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds below the clinical threshold, providing partial confidence in the model. The assessment team notes that the detailed narrative account of the primary comparison activity (including bench protocol, particle count, and Monte Carlo sampling procedure) provides contextual confidence in the result; however, the structured provenance link to the generating computational activity has not been recorded in the evidence package. Notwithstanding this gap, the team accepts the package at the current assurance level for internal review purposes, pending remediation of provenance records and credibility factor gaps before regulatory submission.",
